      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 181: Potential robustness issue: getCollaborativeDocuments() return values are used without strict type conversions/validation. Fields such as \"uri\", \"displayName\", \"author\", \"kind\", and especially \"timestamp\" are taken from the daemon map and used directly (timestamp converted with toLongLong()). If the daemon returns unexpected types or missing fields this can lead to incorrect values (0) or subtle UI issues. Rationale: Inputs from the daemon are untrusted; explicit conversions and fallbacks make behavior deterministic. Suggested change: normalize fields with toString()/toLongLong() and guard timestamp parsing. Example:\n```suggestion\nfor (const auto\u0026 commit : docs) {\n    const QString documentId \u003d commit.value(QStringLiteral(\"uri\")).toString();\n    if (documentId.isEmpty() || seen.contains(documentId))\n        continue;\n    seen.insert(documentId);\n\n    QString name \u003d ConfigurationManager::instance()\n                       .collaborativeDocumentName(accountId, convId, documentId);\n    if (name.isEmpty())\n        name \u003d commit.value(QStringLiteral(\"displayName\")).toString();\n\n    QString author \u003d commit.value(QStringLiteral(\"author\")).toString();\n    QString kind \u003d commit.value(QStringLiteral(\"kind\")).toString();\n    qint64 timestamp \u003d 0;\n    const QVariant tsVar \u003d commit.value(QStringLiteral(\"timestamp\"));\n    if (tsVar.isValid()) {\n        bool ok \u003d false;\n        timestamp \u003d tsVar.toLongLong(\u0026ok);\n        if (!ok) {\n            // attempt fallback from string\n            timestamp \u003d tsVar.toString().toLongLong(\u0026ok);\n            if (!ok) timestamp \u003d 0; // deterministic fallback\n        }\n    }\n\n    QVariantMap entry;\n    entry[QStringLiteral(\"documentId\")] \u003d documentId;\n    entry[QStringLiteral(\"name\")] \u003d name;\n    entry[QStringLiteral(\"author\")] \u003d author;\n    entry[QStringLiteral(\"kind\")] \u003d (kind \u003d\u003d QLatin1String(\"rich\")) ? kind : QLatin1String(\"text\");\n    entry[QStringLiteral(\"hasUpdate\")] \u003d hasUnreadDocumentUpdateForDocument(convId, documentId);\n    entry[QStringLiteral(\"timestamp\")] \u003d timestamp;\n    result.append(entry);\n}\n```",
