      "message": "[error] Line 1045: Critical: New Qt wrapper method getCollaborativeDocuments was added, but the DBus/other ConfigurationManager backends (used in DBus builds) do not appear to expose the same API. This will break DBus builds as noted in the open thread. Rationale: CollaborativeAdapter calls ConfigurationManager::instance().getCollaborativeDocuments() — when ConfigurationManager is provided by the DBus wrapper the symbol must exist. Suggested fix: Add an equivalent getCollaborativeDocuments method to the DBus ConfigurationManager implementation and expose it through the same interface. Example (gerrit-style):\n```suggestion\n// In dbus/configurationmanager.h / corresponding dbus wrapper\nVectorMapStringString getCollaborativeDocuments(const QString\u0026 accountId, const QString\u0026 conversationId)\n{\n    auto docs \u003d libjami::getCollaborativeDocuments(accountId.toStdString(), conversationId.toStdString());\n    return convertVecMap(docs);\n}\n```\nAlso ensure the DBus introspection/signature and binding code are updated so the method is available in DBus builds.",
